cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on the intersection of language and reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach called Textual Hindsight Experience Replay (THER) that extends the Hindsight Experience Replay approach to the language setting, which involves learning from past successful trajectories. This suggests that the paper could also fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also mentions the use of neural architectures, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper deals with interactive agents and instruction following tasks, which could fall under the category of cs.RO (Robotics).
